b'What do you stand for? And how do you stand for it? Here\xe2\x80\x99s how a couple of our Gap HQ employees & their family members\xc2\xa0answered (pictured left to right.)
.
Marino P: \xe2\x80\x9cHarmony.\xc2\xa0Meaning, even though there are obvious and not so obvious differences in people\xe2\x80\x99s thoughts and ideas, making progress together."
.
Jorge O: "I stand for queer rights and for people who can\xe2\x80\x99t vote. I do that by presenting my unapologetic authentic self everywhere as a queer Latinx. And by raising my voice for undocumented Latinx people, and people who live in US territories who don\xe2\x80\x99t have a say on decisions that directly affect them."
.
Susie O: "I stand united with my brown and black people against the racist systems.\xc2\xa0 I stand for it by voting locally to place the right people in office who can make a change within the government and donating to organizations who have been fighting the fight to make this change happen."
.
Teniola A: "I stand for making sure that Gap\xe2\x80\x99s employees want to be here, to grow & truly feel a part of the culture. As the leader of AANG, if I can make anyone at Gap Inc. feel like they belong, I've done my job."'
